  "nursesNote": "Stress is the body and mind's response to demands; some stress is normal, and coping is how a person manages it. The nurse assesses the patient's stressors and current coping. Adaptive (healthy) coping includes problem-solving, exercise, relaxation and deep breathing, mindfulness, talking with support, and time management. Maladaptive coping such as substance use, avoidance, denial, aggression, isolation, or overeating may relieve stress briefly but is harmful over time. The nurse teaches and helps the patient practice healthy coping skills, encourages social support, and works to replace maladaptive patterns with adaptive ones. Care is individualized, and the patient is supported in building skills they can use long-term.",
  "providerOrders": [
    "Assess stressors and current coping",
    "Teach healthy coping and relaxation skills",
    "Encourage social support",
    "Help replace maladaptive coping with adaptive coping",
    "Individualize and reinforce skill practice"
  ],
